    • Constructor Detail

      • ServiceInfo

        public ServiceInfo(java.lang.String image,
                   java.lang.String name,
                   java.lang.String namespace,
                   java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> labels,
                   java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> envs,
                   float cpus,
                   int memMBytes,
                   int replicas,
                   int targetPort,
                   int publishPort,
                   StorageInfo storageInfo,
                   boolean useIngress)
        Non Default Constructor to specify the Service creation information.
        Parameters:
        image - The Image Name.
        name - The Service Name (should be made unique).
        cpus - The CPU's in a percent of a core, this is converted to millicores (multiplied by 1000 in the getter).
        memMBytes - The Memory in Mbytes, this is converted to bytes internally (multiplied by 1000000 in the getter).
        replicas - The number of replicas to create in the Swarm.
        targetPort - The Target Port inside the Container.
        publishPort - The Published Port outside the Container.
        storageInfo - Configuration for the Service Storage
        useIngress - Whether to use NodePorts or ClusterIP(i.e. Reverse Proxy)
